  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and falls under criminal legislation. Money laundering is typically defined as the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear to have been derived from a legitimate source. It is considered a serious financial crime that is often associated with other criminal activities such as drug trafficking, fraud, and organized crime. Most jurisdictions have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations with criminal penalties, including fines and imprisonment, for those convicted of money laundering activities.",
